There is R134 million in total estimated PowerBall jackpots
up for grabs on Friday night. PowerBall is at R40 million and the PowerBall PLUS jackpot
is currently standing at a whopping R94 million, and this could be yours if you
Phanda, Pusha, Play this Friday 08 April. The draw takes place at 9 pm. Charmaine Mabuza, ITHUBA CEO said as both PowerBall and
PowerBall PLUS jackpot continues to grow at a significant rate, they are urging
players to continue to check their tickets after each draw, and to claim their
prizes before their ticket expires. “Furthermore, we also congratulate our latest
multi-millionaire who bagged the LOTTO PLUS 2 – R7 million jackpot from draw
number 2218, which took place this past Wednesday.” She said the ticket was played in Upington with a wager of
R30, the player is encouraged to visit their nearest ITHUBA office to claim
their winnings. To stand a chance of becoming lucky like this latest winner,
buy your PowerBall tickets for Friday’s draw at any National Lottery retailer,
or via one of our banking partners namely Absa, Standard Bank, Nedbank and FNB.
The National Lottery website nationallottery.co.za, via the National Lottery
